================================================================================
3. SCOPE OF COMPLIANCE
================================================================================

3.1 PERSONAL USE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
You may use and modify AOL-Licensed Files privately without attribution, 
licensing, or compliance obligations.

3.2 LIMITED SHARING (Under 25 People, Private)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
You may share AOL-Licensed Files or Derivative Works with fewer than 25 
individuals via private channels without attribution or license compliance 
requirements, provided:

1. Distribution remains private (not publicly accessible)
2. Use is non-commercial
3. Recipients are explicitly identified or access is controlled

No attribution or license headers are required for Limited Sharing.

The authors acknowledge that enforcement of Limited Sharing violations is 
impractical and will not pursue legal action against individuals engaged in 
small-scale, non-commercial private sharing.

3.3 PUBLIC DISTRIBUTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Public Distribution of AOL-Licensed Files requires:

1. Attribution for unmodified or Lightly Modified files (Section 4.3)
2. License preservation - AOL-Licensed Files must maintain AOL license
3. Copyleft for AOL files - Derivative Works of AOL-Licensed Files must be AOL 
   (unless Substantially Modified - see Section 5)
4. Source availability - Source code must be available if binaries are 
   distributed

Dependencies and non-AOL files are NOT subject to AOL requirements (see 
Section 13).

================================================================================
4. LIGHT VS SUBSTANTIALLY MODIFIED WORKS
================================================================================

4.1 LIGHTLY MODIFIED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A modification is Lightly Modified if it affects only cosmetic, non-functional, 
or trivial elements:

EXAMPLES:
- Renaming functions, variables, classes, or files
- Adjusting formatting, indentation, whitespace
- Modifying or adding comments
- Reorganizing code without altering control flow
- Adding wrapper functions that call existing logic unchanged
- Translating variable/function names
- Syntax changes that don't alter behavior (e.g., if/else to ternary)
- Performance optimizations that don't change output

Refactoring without behavior change is Lightly Modified.

4.2 SUBSTANTIALLY MODIFIED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A modification is Substantially Modified if it:

LOGIC CHANGES:
- Alters, rewrites, or extends functional logic
- Changes control flow (loops, conditionals, error handling)
- Modifies algorithms affecting behavior or output
- Changes data structures affecting module behavior

SCOPE CHANGES:
- Adds new modules, classes, or files
- Rewrites more than 30% of lines in an existing file beyond Lightly Modified changes (see Section 4.1)
- Adds new functions to an existing module beyond trivial or cosmetic changes (see Section 4.1)
- Integrates with new dependencies that materially change functionality or behavior

EDGE CASES:
- One-line bug fixes: Lightly Modified
- Multiple edits, whether small or large, that together materially change functionality or behavior: Substantially Modified
- Complete rewrite in a different language: Substantially Modified


4.3 ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

FOR PUBLIC DISTRIBUTION OF LIGHTLY MODIFIED AOL FILES:

Attribution must include:

FILE HEADER:
/*
 * Based on [Original Project] by [Original Author(s)]
 * Licensed under Authentic Open License (AOL)
 * Original source: [URL if available]
 * 
 * Modified by [Your Name] on [Date]
 */

README SECTION:
## Attribution
This project includes code from [Original Project] by [Author(s)],
licensed under AOL.

Original source: [URL]
Modifications: [Brief description]

MINIMUM: File headers for modified files OR prominent README section.

FOR SUBSTANTIALLY MODIFIED WORKS:

Attribution is optional (see Section 5 for relicensing rights).

================================================================================
5. RELICENSING RIGHTS FOR SUBSTANTIAL MODIFICATIONS
================================================================================

5.1 GENERAL PRINCIPLE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
AOL-Licensed Files must remain under AOL, except when Substantially Modified 
as defined below.

5.2 WHEN RELICENSING IS PERMITTED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
You MAY relicense Substantially Modified works to a different license IF all of the following conditions are met:

CONDITION 1: Heavy Modification Threshold
The work contains modifications that are substantive and meaningful according to Section 4.1. Substantive modifications must:

- Alter or improve core algorithms, logic, or control flow
- Add or restructure functionality that materially changes behavior
- Change architecture or design patterns in a way that impacts the file’s operation
- Integrate with new systems or dependencies that affect functionality

Trivial changes, cosmetic edits, or unused code additions do not count, regardless of file size.

CONDITION 2: Copyright Holder Consent
For files with multiple contributors:

- You must own copyright to your modifications
- Relicensing is allowed only if:
  - You obtain consent from all original contributors, OR
  - Your modifications represent a substantial portion of the file’s functional content, OR
  - Original content is negligible (less than 10% of functional content)

CONDITION 3: Attribution Preserved
Even when relicensing, you must preserve attribution:

/*
 * Portions originally from [Original Project] by [Author(s)]
 * Original license: Authentic Open License (AOL)
 * Substantially modified by [Your Name]
 * Current license: [New License]
*/

5.3 WHEN RELICENSING IS NOT PERMITTED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
You may NOT relicense if:

- Modifications are Lightly Modified (cosmetic or trivial)
- Original authors explicitly prohibited relicensing in file headers
- Changes do not meet the Heavy Modification Threshold
- You lack consent from co-contributors where required

5.4 NEW FILES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
New files you create (not derived from AOL-Licensed Files) may use any license you choose.

================================================================================
6. STRONG COPYLEFT FOR AOL FILES
================================================================================

6.1 COPYLEFT REQUIREMENT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
AOL-Licensed Files that are unmodified or Lightly Modified must remain under 
AOL when publicly distributed.

PROHIBITED:
- Removing AOL license headers from AOL files
- Relicensing AOL files under MIT, Apache, BSD, GPL, or proprietary licenses 
  (unless Section 5 applies)
- Distributing AOL files without source code availability

6.2 COPYLEFT DOES NOT APPLY TO:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Dependencies (npm packages, system libraries, etc.)
- New files you create
- Substantially Modified files (if relicensing conditions are met)
- Configuration files or build scripts

